      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Letter not found. The text given here is from 'Answers to correspondents',Leader, 9 March 1895, p. 9 (B95.03.02). It is introduced bySample of Grass.— H.T.,Upper Everton, writes: — "Would you kindly c...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">95.03.00b<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Leader</p>
            <p rend="space"
               style="text-align: center; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letter not found. The text given here is from 'Answers to correspondents',<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Leader</seg>, 9 March 1895, p. 9 (B95.03.02). It is introduced by</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0.5in; text-indent: -0.5in; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-variant: small-caps; ">Sample of Grass</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.— H</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">.T.,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Upper Everton, writes: — "Would you kindly classify the enclosed specimen of grass, which, I believe, were it better known, would be extensively cultivated for cattle fodder. It Is a prolific seed bearer; each seed throwing up an immense number of stems, thick and succulent, of which cattle are very fond, luxuriates in gravelly river flats, growing sometimes, under favorable conditions, to the height of 4 feet or more, and will even thrive in heaps of river gravel, placed in dry positions among the hills, or dry clay banks, appearing to resist heat well, as far as observed in the dry districts of the north-east. Very little moisture causes the seeds to germinate, sometimes in 24 hours, when its growth is very rapid. It will stand close feeding." The grass, Baron von Mueller informs us, is the Pannum Crux Galli,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">[typesetter's error for<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Panicum Crus Galli</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">?]<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">vernacularly known as Cockshin Grass, and it is the variety without long prickles to the spikes, therefore not an objectionable form of this grass.</seg>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">All the praise bestowed by your correspondent on</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">this grass is well deserved. It is a thankful</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">p</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">lant, both in culture and naturalisation, and</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">i</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">n our happy clime we can<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">h</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">a</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">v</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">e it all</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">the year round, whereas in cold zones it is grown as</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">an annual, and gives even there an appreciable</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">return in the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">sh</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">ort, war</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">m</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>season. Originally the</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">P</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">anuu</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">m</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Typesetter's error for<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Panicum</seg>?</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>came from the countries at the Mediterranean Sea and th</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">e</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>war</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">mer<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">regions of Asia, but</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">for centuries i</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">t became already naturalised in</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">America, and we had it here almost since the commencement of colonisation, as by the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">m</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">i</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">n</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">ute hair</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">like spikes the grain bearing particles adhere</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">readily to the e</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">m</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">bo</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">ll</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">a</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">g</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">es. The grain serves also</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">well for small cage birds. This grass is of short</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">duration, but it is always re-established readily</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
               </seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">from it</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">s</seg>
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                  <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>dropping seeds.</seg>
               <seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The same<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>column<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>also contains the following entry:</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0.5in; text-indent: -0.1666in; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-variant: small-caps; ">Specimen of Grass.—</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Observer, Wangoon.—</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">The grass sent from Wangoon, Baron von Mueller</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">states, is also one of t</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">he</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>forms of th</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">e</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>ver</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">y<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">variable</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Pam</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">iu</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">m</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Oxus Gall [typesetter's error for<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Panicum Crus Galli</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">]</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">, so that what<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">h</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">e said about the</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">specimen sent by<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">H</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>T., of Egerton</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">sic</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">?)</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">, will apply also</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">to this one. If the abor</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">i</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">gine</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">s</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>could hav</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">e</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>had this</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">grass centuries ago, it might have helped in leading</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">them up gradually to rural pursuits. At all events</seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">it would have aided in sustaining them.</seg>
                     </p>
                     <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">Panuum</seg>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
